   Beinhoff (neuroimaging).")
(hexCoord ZoneMedicalWing 1 1)

(isa ZoneCulinaryCommons CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneCulinaryCommons ::LABEL "Culinary Commons")
(hasAttribute ZoneCulinaryCommons ::SQ_FT "~3,500 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneCulinaryCommons ::DESCRIPTION
  "Research kitchen + communal dining. Where Taste pillar experiments
   become shared meals. Albert Adria's influence space. Open to the
   entire campus.")
(hexCoord ZoneCulinaryCommons -1 2)
(zonePillar ZoneCulinaryCommons PillarTaste)

(isa ZoneGreenhouse CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneGreenhouse ::LABEL "Greenhouse")
(hasAttribute ZoneGreenhouse ::SQ_FT "~2,000 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneGreenhouse ::DESCRIPTION
  "Controlled-environment agriculture. Plant VOC research, soil sensing,
   atmospheric sampling. Sounder's digital twin of agricultural operations.")
(hexCoord ZoneGreenhouse -2 2)
(zonePillar ZoneGreenhouse PillarSmell)

(isa ZoneMarineLab CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneMarineLab ::LABEL "Marine Lab")
(hasAttribute ZoneMarineLab ::SQ_FT "~2,500 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneMarineLab ::DESCRIPTION
  "Aquatic research. Hydrophone arrays, reef monitoring simulations,
   underwater acoustics. DJ Kim's ocean engineering domain.")
(hexCoord ZoneMarineLab -2 1)
(zonePillar ZoneMarineLab PillarSound)

(isa ZoneConferenceHex CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneConferenceHex ::LABEL "Conference Hex")
(hasAttribute ZoneConferenceHex ::SQ_FT "~3,000 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneConferenceHex ::DESCRIPTION
  "Meeting rooms, presentation theater, Charlotte OS live demo room.
   Where clients see the before/after. ISG pitch room.")
(hexCoord ZoneConferenceHex -1 -1)

(isa ZoneResidenceHex CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneResidenceHex ::LABEL "Residence Hex")
(hasAttribute ZoneResidenceHex ::SQ_FT "~8,000 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneResidenceHex ::DESCRIPTION
  "On-campus housing for visiting researchers, summer interns, and core
   team during intensive sprints. 12 units.")
(hexCoord ZoneResidenceHex 0 -2)

(isa ZoneFitnessRecovery CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneFitnessRecovery ::LABEL "Fitness & Recovery")
(hasAttribute ZoneFitnessRecovery ::SQ_FT "~3,000 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneFitnessRecovery ::DESCRIPTION
  "Gym, recovery room, outdoor training area. Matt Hughes's bodybuilding
   research meets Austin Neibarger's chiropractic expertise. The body
   as research subject.")
(hexCoord ZoneFitnessRecovery 1 -2)

(isa ZoneCommonsLibrary CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneCommonsLibrary ::LABEL "Commons & Library")
(hasAttribute ZoneCommonsLibrary ::SQ_FT "~4,000 sq ft")
(hasAttribute ZoneCommonsLibrary ::DESCRIPTION
  "Open workspace, reference library, whiteboard walls. Where cross-pillar
   conversations happen naturally. Coffee bar.")
(hexCoord ZoneCommonsLibrary 2 -2)


;;; ================================================================
;;; SECTION 5: GREEN SPACES
;;; ================================================================

(isa ZoneCentralGreen CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneCentralGreen ::LABEL "Central Green")
(hasAttribute ZoneCentralGreen ::SQ_FT "~1 acre")
(hasAttribute ZoneCentralGreen ::DESCRIPTION
  "Open lawn. Outdoor events, swarm demonstrations, team gatherings.
   The physical substrate where people collide.")
(hexCoord ZoneCentralGreen 0 2)

(isa ZoneWestGarden CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneWestGarden ::LABEL "West Garden")
(hasAttribute ZoneWestGarden ::SQ_FT "~0.5 acres")
(hasAttribute ZoneWestGarden ::DESCRIPTION "Meditation garden, walking paths, benches. Divergent thinking space.")
(hexCoord ZoneWestGarden -2 0)

(isa ZoneEastMeadow CampusZone)
(hasAttribute ZoneEastMeadow ::LABEL "East Meadow")
(hasAttribute ZoneEastMeadow ::SQ_FT "~1 acre")
(hasAttribute ZoneEastMeadow ::DESCRIPTION
  "Natural area. Wildlife observation, environmental sensor array,
   outdoor acoustics testing.")
(hexCoord ZoneEastMeadow 2 1)


;;; ================================================================
;;; SECTION 6: ADJACENCY EDGES
;;; Two hex cells are adjacent if max(|dq|, |dr|, |dq+dr|) == 1.
;;; ================================================================

;; Center (0,0) → Ring 1
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneSightLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneTouchLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneTasteLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneSoundLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneSmellLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneServerCore ZoneBrainLab)

;; Ring 1 internal adjacencies
(adjacentZone ZoneSightLab ZoneTouchLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneTouchLab ZoneTasteLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneTasteLab ZoneSoundLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneSoundLab ZoneSmellLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneSmellLab ZoneBrainLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneBrainLab ZoneSightLab)

;; Ring 1 → Ring 2
(adjacentZone ZoneSightLab ZoneFabrication)
(adjacentZone ZoneSightLab ZoneMedicalWing)
(adjacentZone ZoneSightLab ZoneDroneField)
(adjacentZone ZoneTouchLab ZoneMedicalWing)
(adjacentZone ZoneTouchLab ZoneCulinaryCommons)
(adjacentZone ZoneTouchLab ZoneCentralGreen)
(adjacentZone ZoneTasteLab ZoneCulinaryCommons)
(adjacentZone ZoneTasteLab ZoneGreenhouse)
(adjacentZone ZoneTasteLab ZoneMarineLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneSoundLab ZoneMarineLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneSoundLab ZoneWestGarden)
(adjacentZone ZoneSoundLab ZoneConferenceHex)
(adjacentZone ZoneSmellLab ZoneConferenceHex)
(adjacentZone ZoneSmellLab ZoneResidenceHex)
(adjacentZone ZoneSmellLab ZoneBrainLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneBrainLab ZoneFitnessRecovery)
(adjacentZone ZoneBrainLab ZoneCommonsLibrary)
(adjacentZone ZoneBrainLab ZoneDroneField)

;; Ring 2 internal adjacencies
(adjacentZone ZoneFabrication ZoneDroneField)
(adjacentZone ZoneFabrication ZoneMedicalWing)
(adjacentZone ZoneFabrication ZoneEastMeadow)
(adjacentZone ZoneMedicalWing ZoneCentralGreen)
(adjacentZone ZoneCulinaryCommons ZoneGreenhouse)
(adjacentZone ZoneCulinaryCommons ZoneCentralGreen)
(adjacentZone ZoneGreenhouse ZoneMarineLab)
(adjacentZone ZoneMarineLab ZoneWestGarden)
(adjacentZone ZoneConferenceHex ZoneResidenceHex)
(adjacentZone ZoneConferenceHex ZoneWestGarden)
(adjacentZone ZoneResidenceHex ZoneFitnessRecovery)
(adjacentZone ZoneFitnessRecovery ZoneCommonsLibrary)
(adjacentZone ZoneCommonsLibrary ZoneDroneField)
(adjacentZone ZoneDroneField ZoneEastMeadow)


;;; ================================================================
;;; SECTION 7: CAMPUS DESIGN PRINCIPLES
;;; ================================================================

(comment SumAIOASISCampusMt
  "Central Place Theory: the server core sits at the geographic center.
   Six pillar labs surround it at equal distance. Shared facilities fill
   the interstitial hexes. Every point on campus is within 2 hex-steps
   of the core and 1 hex-step of a pillar lab. The property is designed
   so Charlotte can observe the entire campus as a living substrate —
   every building, every room, every researcher is a NODE emitting SIGNALs.")


